Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree

Class EventTreeStatus

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.etree.EventTreeStatus
public class EventTreeStatus extends Object
A wrapper around a status object used by an event tree builder to keep track of how many branches of an event tree have been built.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

  • Method Details

    • getCompleteBranches

      public int getCompleteBranches()
      Returns the number of branches the event tree builder has finished building.
      Returns:
      the number of completed branches

    • incrementCompleteBranches

      public void incrementCompleteBranches()
      Increments the number of branches the event tree builder has finished building by one. This should be called right before finishing a branch.

    • getTotalBranches

      public int getTotalBranches()
      Returns the number of branches the event tree builder has started building (including branches which have finished building).
      Returns:
      the number of started branches

    • incrementTotalBranches

      public void incrementTotalBranches()
      Increments the number of branches the event tree builder has started building by one. This should be called right as the builder begins building a new branch.
